{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"SCOPE EXPANSION (operator-approved, this session 2026-07-15) — validity basis moves from an LLM-only kappa gate to HUMAN-ADJUDICATED ground truth.\n\nWHY: the A/B Cohen's kappa fell 0.74 -> 0.60 -> 0.50 as the usable-pair count grew. A kappa that decays with n is the small-sample-luck signature; true LLM inter-rater agreement here is genuinely moderate (~0.5), i.e. adjudicating gate findings as TP/FP is substantively subjective for a real fraction of findings. That is itself a calibration-relevant finding (a noise band exists), not a bug to tune away. Continuing to edit rubrics until kappa clears 0.7 would be training-on-the-test-set (a tuned kappa is a worthless trust signal), AND the original plan already sanctioned a failed gate as a documentable outcome — so kappa-chasing was both scope creep and a threat to corpus integrity. Operator directed: invest to reach a genuinely-usable corpus via human adjudication of the disputed labels over a constrained sample.\n\nNEW VALIDITY BASIS (replaces the kappa>=0.7 pass/fail gate; AC edit pending before close):\n1. Report A/B kappa HONESTLY as the LLM-reproducibility signal, stratified by source (surfaced vs dropped) — disclosure, not a ship/discard gate. (Dropped-lens polarity is the dominant confound: \"spurious+dropped = good drop = TP\" inverts the surfaced lens; one rubric clarification was applied to remove that genuine ambiguity, disclosed, and will NOT be iterated further.)\n2. HUMAN ADJUDICATION of the contested findings is the authoritative ground truth: A/B disagreements are clustered into distinct dispute archetypes (near-duplicate findings within the same source+criterion collapse to one representative; the human verdict propagates to all members, every member's text shown so propagation is auditable) so the operator adjudicates each DISTINCT dispute once, never the same boilerplate finding repeatedly. Operator adjudicates -> folded back as the final gold label.\n\nHARNESS ROBUSTNESS FIX (found while investigating): adjudicate.py did a single terminal atomic write — all-or-nothing over a ~500-call, ~25-min serialized pass, which also defeated its own resumable design (a mid-run death persisted zero labels; observed: 0 bytes on disk after hundreds of billable calls). Fixed with incremental atomic checkpointing every 5 labels (crash-safe + resumable-for-real); named the append-only-journal / keyed-store pattern as the answer for a genuinely large corpus. Smoke-tested green.\n\nNEW/CHANGED ARTIFACTS: adjudicate.py (checkpointing); cluster_disputes.py (dispute archetype clustering + human worksheet); apply_adjudications.py (fold human verdicts -> final gold labels); README validity section rewritten; kappa.py stays (now reporting, stratified) not a hard gate."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784169991562175001,"uuid":"36e6563e-faf5-4023-a178-778ec16d366f"}